Third-party data and assets:

* NASA JPL Horizons ephemeris (https://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/horizons/) — U.S.
  Government works, public domain in the United States.

* NASA imagery used in the Encyclopedia (photojournal.jpl.nasa.gov,
  images.nasa.gov) — public domain unless an individual asset states
  otherwise. Credits are preserved alongside each image in the UI.

* MAESTRO v3.0.0 (Magenta / Google) — Creative Commons Attribution-
  NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).
  See `data/external_midi/maestro-v3.0.0/LICENSE`. Any LSTM checkpoint
  trained on MAESTRO data inherits the NC clause and MAY NOT be
  redistributed in a commercial deployment. The default
  `note_lstm_style_planet.pt` checkpoint is trained only on
  NASA-derived sequences and is not subject to this restriction.

* FluidR3 GM SoundFont (optional) — see the project's own license terms
  before redistributing.
